    "intended": "Let $A\\subseteq \\mathbb{N}$ be a set such that $\\lvert A\\cap [1,x]\\rvert=o(x^{1/2})$. Let\\[B=\\{ n\\geq 1 : a\\nmid n\\textrm{ for all }a\\in A\\}.\\]If $B=\\{b_1<b_2<\\cdots\\}$ then is it true that\\[\\lim \\frac{1}{x}\\sum_{b_i<x}(b_{i+1}-b_i)^2\\]exists (and is finite)?",
